form.name: Electromagnetic Multipoles
form.description: The multipoles can be given in 4 unique sets of isospin or charge channels: a_1 x_1 + a_2 x_2 + . . . + a_{n-1} x_{n-1} + a_n x_n = \sum_{I=1}^{n} a_i x_i
form.references: D. Drechsel and L. Tiator, J. Phys. G 18 (1992) 449-497  \href{https://maid.kph.uni-mainz.de/JPhysG18/JPhysG18.pdf}{[pdf]}
